CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 5, 1974, pg. 1 reads: "...Center, Minister Hassain leaves Muhammad's Temple..."  Quote from member of public: "Muhammad's Imports brought in metric tons of whiting fish from Peru. Our sales force inspired Robert Wholey to market Whiting fish more aggressively. We took 'fish' door-to-door as a means of providing income for African Americans" -
TitMainTitle: Robert X Davenport or Imam Robert Hassain on sidewalk in front of Muhammad's Temple No. 22, at 722 Kelly Street and Homewood Avenue, Homewood
